---
import DocsLayout from '../../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro'
---
<DocsLayout title="Lazy Load Plugin">
  <h1>Lazy Load</h1>
  <p class="lead">IntersectionObserver-based lazy loading. Images and background elements load only when they approach the viewport. Falls back to immediate loading in browsers without <code>IntersectionObserver</code>.</p>

  <h2>Import</h2>
  <pre><code>import {"{"} lazyLoad {"}"} from '@andresclua/sliderkit-plugins'</code></pre>

  <h2>Options</h2>
  <table>
    <thead><tr><th>Option</th><th>Type</th><th>Default</th><th>Description</th></tr></thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td><code>selector</code></td><td><code>string</code></td><td><code>'[data-src]'</code></td><td>CSS selector used to find lazy-loadable elements inside each slide.</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>rootMargin</code></td><td><code>string</code></td><td><code>'200px'</code></td><td>Margin passed to <code>IntersectionObserver</code>. Larger values pre-load elements further from the viewport.</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h2>How it works</h2>
  <p>Use <code>data-src</code> instead of <code>src</code> on <code>&lt;img&gt;</code> elements (or any element for background images). When the element intersects, the plugin moves the value to <code>src</code> or <code>background-image</code>, removes <code>data-src</code>, and adds the class <code>c--slider-a--loaded</code>.</p>

  <h2>Example</h2>
  <pre><code>{`<!-- HTML -->
<div id="my-slider">
  <div class="slide"><img data-src="/photo-1.jpg" alt="Photo 1" /></div>
  <div class="slide"><img data-src="/photo-2.jpg" alt="Photo 2" /></div>
</div>

<!-- JS -->
import { createSlider } from '@andresclua/sliderkit'
import { lazyLoad } from '@andresclua/sliderkit-plugins'

createSlider('#my-slider', {
  plugins: [lazyLoad({ rootMargin: '300px' })],
})`}</code></pre>

  <p><a href="/demos/lazy-load">View lazy load demo</a></p>
</DocsLayout>
